<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRANSTON AND LINCOLN S&amp;L DEBACLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I was saddened when I read your article about an elderly man taking his life 
over the Lincoln S&amp;L debacle. So many in this great nation have been 
impacted by the raping and pilfering of our nation's banks over the last 10 
years. 
</P>
<P>
It seems to me that our country has slid from its stature. We idolize the power 
and wealth of such figures as Donald Trump, Michael Milken, Charles Keating and 
Oliver North. Yet not long ago these men would have been hung, not as heroes, 
but as the villains and criminals they are. These men produce nothing and suck 
the very vitality from the average American person today. Our government is no 
better. Today, instead of a leader, we elected an indecisive follower. 
</P>
<P>
I am further saddened that the baby-boom generation has no leaders in its fold. 
Yet we have the insurmountable task of bringing America from the trillions of 
dollars in debt that recent administrations have bequeathed to us. I see a 
rough road ahead, and no one who is capable of rallying this nation back to its 
roots. May God help us. 
</P>
<P>
MICHAEL W. FISHER 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach 
</P>
