<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SUSPICIOUS HOUSE FIRE KILLS 2 MEN, INJURES 
1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A suspicious early-morning fire swept through a one-bedroom home in the Lennox 
area Friday, killing two men and injuring another, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The dead, reported to be undocumented workers in their late 20s, were not 
immediately identified because of the extent of their burns, the coroner's 
office said. 
</P>
<P>
The victims were living in a small house in the 10700 block of Inglewood 
Avenue, along with five other men. 
</P>
<P>
The house was burning furiously when firefighters arrived at around 3 a.m., 
fire officials said. After putting out the blaze in about 20 minutes, searchers 
found one man dead in the bedroom. The other was found in a sleeping area on 
the back porch. 
</P>
<P>
The fire apparently started in the kitchen and was of suspicious origin, a 
Sheriff's Department spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
