<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 800 PUPILS EVACUATED AFTER DISCOVERY OF 
BOMB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 800 children were evacuated Friday from the Del Sur Elementary School in 
Lancaster after discovery of a potentially lethal time bomb, made by a 
10-year-old boy who said he learned how from a TV secret agent show, the 
sheriff's bomb squad said. 
</P>
<P>
The boy was unable, however, to determine when the bomb was timed to explode, 
which turned out to be minutes after they confiscated it, deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
A boy wearing a Bart Simpson T-shirt was taken into custody after admitting he 
built the bomb from model rocket engines and a digital alarm clock. He said he 
used information from an episode of the "MacGyver" TV show. The show's producer 
said there was no such episode. 
</P>
<P>
The bomb was discovered by third-graders in the boys' restroom shortly after 10 
a.m. and exploded by the bomb squad on the school playground at 11:05, just six 
minutes before it would have gone off, a deputy said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
EVACUATIONS; LOS ANGELES COUNTY -- SCHOOLS; STUDENTS -- LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 
BOMBS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
