<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: GIRL, 14, FOUND DEAD IN BEDROOM OF HER HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sheriff's homicide investigators were looking into the death of a 14-year-old 
East Los Angeles girl who was found dead in a rear bedroom of her small home on 
South Gage Avenue Friday when a classmate stopped by to accompany her to 
school, the Sheriff's Department reported. 
</P>
<P>
The girl, identified as Maribel Perez, may have been strangled, according to 
the coroner's office. Sheriff's homicide detectives were assigned to the case, 
but no other details were available, according to Deputy Larry Mead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
