<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: BAVARO AGREES TO PAY FINE FOR BUMPING OFFICIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tight end Mark Bavaro of the New York Giants agreed Friday to pay a fine of a 
reported $7,500 levied by the NFL for bumping an official during a 31-13 loss 
to the Philadelphia Eagles on Nov. 25. 
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred seconds after the Eagles' Byron Evans returned an 
interception 22 yards for a touchdown. When Bavaro became involved in a shoving 
match, umpire Dave Hamilton ended up on the ground after either tripping or 
being pushed inadvertently. 
</P>
