<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANGELS AGREE TO TERMS WITH MANRIQUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Angels announced Friday they had agreed to terms with free-agent infielder 
Fred Manrique and had offered arbitration to free agents Donnie Hill and Max 
Venable. 
</P>
<P>
Manrique hit .237 for the Texas Rangers and Minnesota Twins last season. He was 
sent to Minnesota's triple-A affiliate in Portland, Ore., in July and was not 
recalled. 
</P>
<P>
Hill and Venable have until Dec. 19 to accept or reject arbitration. If they do 
not accept it, the Angels may negotiate with them until Jan. 8. If they do not 
sign by that date, they would be unable to re-sign with the Angels until May 1. 
HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
BASEBALL PLAYERS -- CONTRACTS; ARBITRATION; CALIFORNIA ANGELS (BASEBALL TEAM); 
HILL, DONNIE; VENABLE, MAX; MANRIQUE, FRED 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
