<HEADLINE>
<P>
VITAL SIGN FACES NINE TONIGHT IN $334,000 ED BURKE FUTURITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The outstanding 2-year-old colt Vital Sign, a winner of over $205,000 in his 
young career, takes on nine rivals tonight in the $334,000 Ed Burke Futurity at 
Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
Vital Sign, trained by Lee Roy Heidleberg, comes into the Ed Burke Futurity 
after a very close second place finish in the $140,000 Breeders Juvenile 
Classic on Nov. 17 at Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
Vital Sign followed that effort with an impressive victory in his Ed Burke 
trial when he scored a three-quarter length win in a time of 17.74 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
Vital Sign, who will be ridden by Steve Treasure, will start from the inside 
post tonight. His challengers include A One Man Band, Good Barry, BF First 
Lien, Reeds Signature, Shawnes Diamond, Dash For Time, Dashes Dish, Tolls Touch 
and Jacks Dash. 
</P>
</TEXT>
