<TEXT>
<P>
Mortgage Rates Lower: Fixed-rate mortgages averaged 9.81% this week, down from 
9.9% last week, according to a national survey released by the Federal Home 
Loan Mortgage Corp. The rate was the lowest since rates averaged 9.8% last 
January. On one-year adjustable rate mortgages, lenders were asking an average 
initial rate of 8.04%, down from 8.08% last week. The rates do not include 
add-on fees known as points. 
</P>
