<HEADLINE>
<P>
A SEASON TO SING AND DANCE ABOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Care to crack "The Nutcracker"? Yearn to sing along to Handel's "Messiah"? Do 
visions of Scrooge and Daddy Warbucks dance in your head? 
</P>
<P>
A number of major holiday offerings in Southern California begin this weekend. 
There are at least a dozen "Nutcracker" ballet offerings, in everything from 
school productions to million-dollar opera-house stagings, along with another 
dozen "Messiahs" in a variety of versions. And "Annie" and "A Christmas Carol" 
can be found all over the Southland. 
</P>
<P>
A guide to this season's fare is on F10. 
</P>
