<P>
PREP BASKETBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the Garden Grove tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Western 69, Magnolia 38 -- Western (4-0) powered its way to the championship at 
Garden Grove High School. 
</P>
<P>
Magnolia (3-1), which upset Laguna Hills Thursday, was unable to handle the 
Pioneers' full-court pressure and height advantage and fell behind, 14-5, in 
the first quarter. After a brief rally that closed the gap to 18-15 early in 
the second quarter, Magnolia was never close again. 
</P>
<P>
In the third-place game, Laguna Hills nipped Buena Park, 73-71, as Brian Matsen 
scored 36 points including the winning basket at the buzzer. Garden Grove 
defeated Bolsa Grande, 66-54, in the consolation finals. 
</P>
<P>
Thomas Barraza led Western with 24 points and six assists. TOM BIRSCHBACH 
</P>
