<BYLINE>
<P>
By STUART MATTHEWS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the Valencia boys' tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Servite 59, Westminster 48 -- Servite used a stifling man-to-man defense to 
defeat undersized Westminster, 59-48, for the championship of the Valencia 
tournament at Valencia High. 
</P>
<P>
Adam Anderson, the only returning starter from Servite's Division III state 
champion team, led the Friars (4-0) with 19 points. 
</P>
<P>
Anderson, a swingman, added eight steals and was named the tournament's most 
valuable player. 
</P>
<P>
Guard Matt Kenney scored 16 for Servite and center Ryan Dodd added 10. 
</P>
<P>
Westminster is 2-2. 
</P>
<P>
Esperanza 81, Cypress 48 -- Forward Joe Foss scored a tournament-high 36 points 
to pace the Aztecs in the third-place game. 
</P>
<P>
Katella 82, La Habra 60 -- The Knights were led by Kevin Carlson's 22 points in 
the consolation championship. 
</P>
<P>
Valencia 80, Santa Ana 77 -- Santa Ana's furious rally -- it outscored 
Valencia, 35-22, in the fourth quarter -- fell short and Valencia won the 
fifth-place game. The Saints are 1-2. STUART MATTHEWS 
</P>
