<HEADLINE>
<P>
PERFORMING ARTS CENTER WOES NO SURPRISE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The woes of the Orange County Performing Arts Center ("O.C.'s Arts Center Has 
Fallen on Hard Times" by Mark I. Pinsky, Nov. 29) come as little surprise. I 
subscribed to one of the opening series, my seats downgraded when a 
contribution letter sent to me with my order acknowledgment went unfulfilled. 
</P>
<P>
We sat "in the rafters" in an almost empty section; the acoustics were not as 
good as what we were expecting. We are called six to eight times a year for 
donations. 
</P>
<P>
We support the arts. We think nothing of attending the Hollywood Bowl or the 
Shubert or Ahmanson. We thoroughly enjoy South Coast Repertory, both Mainstage 
and Second Stage. But did the population numbers warrant another performing 
arts center? Or was it artistic and political egos competing with Los Angeles? 
</P>
<P>
SUSAN KNIGHT 
</P>
<P>
Orange 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, An Orange resident complains of being seated "in the rafters" of OCPAC. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
