<HEADLINE>
<P>
CATALOGUING THE WATER LILY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Marilyn Pitts 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The water lily season is nearing its end, but there is no reason to wait for 
spring. Just as there is the Burpee's seed catalogue for the home gardener, 
there are water garden catalogues for the water lily enthusiast to ponder over 
during the winter months. 
</P>
<P>
Here are several water gardens that offer mail-order service to California: 
</P>
<P>
Lilypons Water Gardens, 1626 Lilypons Road, Brookshire, Tex. 77423-0188. 
</P>
<P>
Paradise Water Gardens, 14 May St., Whitman, Mass. 02382. 
</P>
<P>
Van Ness Water Gardens, 2460 N. Euclid Ave., Upland, Calif. 91786. 
</P>
<P>
Waterford Gardens, 74 E. Allendale Road, Saddle River, N.J. 07458. 
</P>
<P>
William Tricker Inc., 7125 Tanglewood Drive, Independence, Ohio 44131. 
</P>
<P>
If you are interested in further information on water lilies and related 
activities, contact the International Water Lily Society, c/o School of 
Science, Southwest Texas State University, San Marcos, Tex. 78666-4616. Marilyn 
Pitts 
</P>
</TEXT>
